headline: Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS) Sees 13% Weekly Dip; Deputy CFO Resigns
summary: Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS) experienced a share price decline of 13% over the past week. This may be partly linked to the resignation of Raja Akram, Deputy Chief Financial Officer, and strategic discussions about selling a stake in PNE AG, a German renewable developer. The company's stock price was also caught in the broader market downturn, as major indexes like the Dow Jones, S&P 500, and Nasdaq saw substantial declines due to escalating trade tensions and new tariffs. The overall market...
